147NO_RETURN_DUE_TO_CRASH NEVER_INLINE static void crashBecausePageIsSuspended()
148{
149 WTFLogAlways("Error: Attempt to call WKPageRef API/SPI on a suspended page, this is a client bug.");
150 CRASH();
151}
152
153#define CRASH_IF_SUSPENDED if (UNLIKELY(pageRef && toImpl(pageRef)->isSuspended())) \
154 crashBecausePageIsSuspended()

176void WKPageLoadURL(WKPageRef pageRef, WKURLRef URLRef)
177{
178 CRASH_IF_SUSPENDED;
179 toImpl(pageRef)->loadRequest(URL(URL(), toWTFString(URLRef)));
180}
181
182void WKPageLoadURLWithShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy(WKPageRef pageRef, WKURLRef URLRef, bool shouldOpenExternalURLs)
183{
184 CRASH_IF_SUSPENDED;
185 WebCore::ShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy = shouldOpenExternalURLs ? WebCore::ShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy::ShouldAllow : WebCore::ShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy::ShouldNotAllow;
186 toImpl(pageRef)->loadRequest(URL(URL(), toWTFString(URLRef)), shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy);
187}

191 CRASH_IF_SUSPENDED;

193}

232
233static String encodingOf(const String& string)
234{
235 if (string.isNull() || !string.is8Bit())
236 return "utf-16"_s;
237 return "latin1"_s;
238}
239
240static IPC::DataReference dataFrom(const String& string)
241{
242 if (string.isNull() || !string.is8Bit())
243 return { reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(string.characters16()), string.length() * sizeof(UChar) };
244 return { string.characters8(), string.length() * sizeof(LChar) };
245}
246
247static void loadString(WKPageRef pageRef, WKStringRef stringRef, const String& mimeType, const String& baseURL, WKTypeRef userDataRef)
248{
249 String string = toWTFString(stringRef);
250 toImpl(pageRef)->loadData(dataFrom(string), mimeType, encodingOf(string), baseURL, toImpl(userDataRef));
251}

257}

271void WKPageLoadAlternateHTMLStringWithUserData(WKPageRef pageRef, WKStringRef htmlStringRef, WKURLRef baseURLRef, WKURLRef unreachableURLRef, WKTypeRef userDataRef)
272{
273 CRASH_IF_SUSPENDED;

276}

308void WKPageReload(WKPageRef pageRef)
309{
310 CRASH_IF_SUSPENDED;
311 OptionSet<WebCore::ReloadOption> reloadOptions;
312#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
313 if (linkedOnOrAfter(WebCore::SDKVersion::FirstWithExpiredOnlyReloadBehavior))
314 reloadOptions.add(WebCore::ReloadOption::ExpiredOnly);
315#endif
316
317 toImpl(pageRef)->reload(reloadOptions);
318}

365void WKPageGoBack(WKPageRef pageRef)
366{
367 CRASH_IF_SUSPENDED;
368 auto& page = *toImpl(pageRef);
369 if (page.pageClient().hasSafeBrowsingWarning()) {
370 WKPageReload(pageRef);
371 return;
372 }
373 page.goBack();
374}

519WKTypeRef WKPageCopySessionState(WKPageRef pageRef, void* context, WKPageSessionStateFilterCallback filter)
520{
521 // FIXME: This is a hack to make sure we return a WKDataRef to maintain compatibility with older versions of Safari.
522 bool shouldReturnData = !(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(context) & 1);
523 context = reinterpret_cast<void*>(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(context) & ~1);
524
525 auto sessionState = toImpl(pageRef)->sessionState([pageRef, context, filter](WebBackForwardListItem& item) {
526 if (filter) {
527 if (!filter(pageRef, WKPageGetSessionBackForwardListItemValueType(), toAPI(&item), context))
528 return false;
529
530 if (!filter(pageRef, WKPageGetSessionHistoryURLValueType(), toURLRef(item.originalURL().impl()), context))
531 return false;
532 }
533
534 return true;
535 });
536
537 auto data = encodeLegacySessionState(sessionState);
538 if (shouldReturnData)
539 return toAPI(data.leakRef());
540
541 return toAPI(&API::SessionState::create(WTFMove(sessionState)).leakRef());
542}
543
544static void restoreFromSessionState(WKPageRef pageRef, WKTypeRef sessionStateRef, bool navigate)
545{
546 SessionState sessionState;
547
548 // FIXME: This is for backwards compatibility with Safari. Remove it once Safari no longer depends on it.
549 if (toImpl(sessionStateRef)->type() == API::Object::Type::Data) {
550 if (!decodeLegacySessionState(toImpl(static_cast<WKDataRef>(sessionStateRef))->bytes(), toImpl(static_cast<WKDataRef>(sessionStateRef))->size(), sessionState))
551 return;
552 } else {
553 ASSERT(toImpl(sessionStateRef)->type() == API::Object::Type::SessionState);
554
555 sessionState = toImpl(static_cast<WKSessionStateRef>(sessionStateRef))->sessionState();
556 }
557
558 toImpl(pageRef)->restoreFromSessionState(WTFMove(sessionState), navigate);
559}
560
561void WKPageRestoreFromSessionState(WKPageRef pageRef, WKTypeRef sessionStateRef)
562{
563 CRASH_IF_SUSPENDED;
564 restoreFromSessionState(pageRef, sessionStateRef, true);
565}
566
567void WKPageRestoreFromSessionStateWithoutNavigation(WKPageRef pageRef, WKTypeRef sessionStateRef)
568{
569 CRASH_IF_SUSPENDED;
570 restoreFromSessionState(pageRef, sessionStateRef, false);
571}

776void WKPageSetPaginationMode(WKPageRef pageRef, WKPaginationMode paginationMode)
777{
778 CRASH_IF_SUSPENDED;
779 WebCore::Pagination::Mode mode;
780 switch (paginationMode) {
781 case kWKPaginationModeUnpaginated:
782 mode = WebCore::Pagination::Unpaginated;
783 break;
784 case kWKPaginationModeLeftToRight:
785 mode = WebCore::Pagination::LeftToRightPaginated;
786 break;
787 case kWKPaginationModeRightToLeft:
788 mode = WebCore::Pagination::RightToLeftPaginated;
789 break;
790 case kWKPaginationModeTopToBottom:
791 mode = WebCore::Pagination::TopToBottomPaginated;
792 break;
793 case kWKPaginationModeBottomToTop:
794 mode = WebCore::Pagination::BottomToTopPaginated;
795 break;
796 default:
797 return;
798 }
799 toImpl(pageRef)->setPaginationMode(mode);
800}
801
802WKPaginationMode WKPageGetPaginationMode(WKPageRef pageRef)
803{
804 switch (toImpl(pageRef)->paginationMode()) {
805 case WebCore::Pagination::Unpaginated:
806 return kWKPaginationModeUnpaginated;
807 case WebCore::Pagination::LeftToRightPaginated:
808 return kWKPaginationModeLeftToRight;
809 case WebCore::Pagination::RightToLeftPaginated:
810 return kWKPaginationModeRightToLeft;
811 case WebCore::Pagination::TopToBottomPaginated:
812 return kWKPaginationModeTopToBottom;
813 case WebCore::Pagination::BottomToTopPaginated:
814 return kWKPaginationModeBottomToTop;
815 }
816
817 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
818 return kWKPaginationModeUnpaginated;
819}

933void WKPageSetPageContextMenuClient(WKPageRef pageRef, const WKPageContextMenuClientBase* wkClient)
934{
935 CRASH_IF_SUSPENDED;
936#if ENABLE(CONTEXT_MENUS)
937 class ContextMenuClient final : public API::Client<WKPageContextMenuClientBase>, public API::ContextMenuClient {
938 public:
939 explicit ContextMenuClient(const WKPageContextMenuClientBase* client)
940 {
941 initialize(client);
942 }
943
944 private:
945 void getContextMenuFromProposedMenu(WebPageProxy& page, Vector<Ref<WebKit::WebContextMenuItem>>&& proposedMenuVector, WebKit::WebContextMenuListenerProxy& contextMenuListener, const WebHitTestResultData& hitTestResultData, API::Object* userData) override
946 {
947 if (m_client.base.version >= 4 && m_client.getContextMenuFromProposedMenuAsync) {
948 Vector<RefPtr<API::Object>> proposedMenuItems;
949 proposedMenuItems.reserveInitialCapacity(proposedMenuVector.size());
950
951 for (const auto& menuItem : proposedMenuVector)
952 proposedMenuItems.uncheckedAppend(menuItem.ptr());
953
954 auto webHitTestResult = API::HitTestResult::create(hitTestResultData);
955 m_client.getContextMenuFromProposedMenuAsync(toAPI(&page), toAPI(API::Array::create(WTFMove(proposedMenuItems)).ptr()), toAPI(&contextMenuListener), toAPI(webHitTestResult.ptr()), toAPI(userData), m_client.base.clientInfo);
956 return;
957 }
958
959 if (!m_client.getContextMenuFromProposedMenu && !m_client.getContextMenuFromProposedMenu_deprecatedForUseWithV0) {
960 contextMenuListener.useContextMenuItems(WTFMove(proposedMenuVector));
961 return;
962 }
963
964 if (m_client.base.version >= 2 && !m_client.getContextMenuFromProposedMenu) {
965 contextMenuListener.useContextMenuItems(WTFMove(proposedMenuVector));
966 return;
967 }
968
969 Vector<RefPtr<API::Object>> proposedMenuItems;
970 proposedMenuItems.reserveInitialCapacity(proposedMenuVector.size());
971
972 for (const auto& menuItem : proposedMenuVector)
973 proposedMenuItems.uncheckedAppend(menuItem.ptr());
974
975 WKArrayRef newMenu = nullptr;
976 if (m_client.base.version >= 2) {
977 auto webHitTestResult = API::HitTestResult::create(hitTestResultData);
978 m_client.getContextMenuFromProposedMenu(toAPI(&page), toAPI(API::Array::create(WTFMove(proposedMenuItems)).ptr()), &newMenu, toAPI(webHitTestResult.ptr()), toAPI(userData), m_client.base.clientInfo);
979 } else
980 m_client.getContextMenuFromProposedMenu_deprecatedForUseWithV0(toAPI(&page), toAPI(API::Array::create(WTFMove(proposedMenuItems)).ptr()), &newMenu, toAPI(userData), m_client.base.clientInfo);
981
982 RefPtr<API::Array> array = adoptRef(toImpl(newMenu));
983
984 Vector<Ref<WebContextMenuItem>> customMenu;
985 size_t newSize = array ? array->size() : 0;
986 customMenu.reserveInitialCapacity(newSize);
987 for (size_t i = 0; i < newSize; ++i) {
988 WebContextMenuItem* item = array->at<WebContextMenuItem>(i);
989 if (!item) {
990 LOG(ContextMenu, "New menu entry at index %i is not a WebContextMenuItem", (int)i);
991 continue;
992 }
993
994 customMenu.uncheckedAppend(*item);
995 }
996
997 contextMenuListener.useContextMenuItems(WTFMove(customMenu));
998 }

1303 // for backwards compatibility.

2136 static WKAutoplayEventFlags toWKAutoplayEventFlags(OptionSet<WebCore::AutoplayEventFlags> flags)
2137 {
2138 WKAutoplayEventFlags wkFlags = kWKAutoplayEventFlagsNone;
2139 if (flags.contains(WebCore::AutoplayEventFlags::HasAudio))
2140 wkFlags |= kWKAutoplayEventFlagsHasAudio;
2141 if (flags.contains(WebCore::AutoplayEventFlags::PlaybackWasPrevented))
2142 wkFlags |= kWKAutoplayEventFlagsPlaybackWasPrevented;
2143 if (flags.contains(WebCore::AutoplayEventFlags::MediaIsMainContent))
2144 wkFlags |= kWKAutoplayEventFlagsMediaIsMainContent;
2145
2146 return wkFlags;
2147 }
2148
2149 static WKAutoplayEvent toWKAutoplayEvent(WebCore::AutoplayEvent event)
2150 {
2151 switch (event) {
2152 case WebCore::AutoplayEvent::DidAutoplayMediaPastThresholdWithoutUserInterference:
2153 return kWKAutoplayEventDidAutoplayMediaPastThresholdWithoutUserInterference;
2154 case WebCore::AutoplayEvent::DidPlayMediaWithUserGesture:
2155 return kWKAutoplayEventDidPlayMediaWithUserGesture;
2156 case WebCore::AutoplayEvent::DidPreventMediaFromPlaying:
2157 return kWKAutoplayEventDidPreventFromAutoplaying;
2158 case WebCore::AutoplayEvent::UserDidInterfereWithPlayback:
2159 return kWKAutoplayEventUserDidInterfereWithPlayback;
2160 }
2161
2162 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2163 }
2164
2165 void handleAutoplayEvent(WebPageProxy& page, WebCore::AutoplayEvent event, OptionSet<WebCore::AutoplayEventFlags> flags) final
2166 {
2167 if (!m_client.handleAutoplayEvent)
2168 return;
2169
2170 m_client.handleAutoplayEvent(toAPI(&page), toWKAutoplayEvent(event), toWKAutoplayEventFlags(flags), m_client.base.clientInfo);
2171 }

2408
2409 void contentRuleListNotification(WebPageProxy& page, URL&& url, ContentRuleListResults&& results) final
2410 {
2411 if (!m_client.contentRuleListNotification)
2412 return;
2413
2414 Vector<RefPtr<API::Object>> apiListIdentifiers;
2415 Vector<RefPtr<API::Object>> apiNotifications;
2416 for (const auto& pair : results.results) {
2417 const String& listIdentifier = pair.first;
2418 const auto& result = pair.second;
2419 for (const String& notification : result.notifications) {
2420 apiListIdentifiers.append(API::String::create(listIdentifier));
2421 apiNotifications.append(API::String::create(notification));
2422 }
2423 }
2424
2425 if (!apiNotifications.isEmpty())
2426 m_client.contentRuleListNotification(toAPI(&page), toURLRef(url.string().impl()), toAPI(API::Array::create(WTFMove(apiListIdentifiers)).ptr()), toAPI(API::Array::create(WTFMove(apiNotifications)).ptr()), m_client.base.clientInfo);
2427 }
2428 };
2429
2430 WebPageProxy* webPageProxy = toImpl(pageRef);
2431
2432 webPageProxy->setNavigationClient(makeUniqueRef<NavigationClient>(wkClient));
2433}

2919WKScrollPinningBehavior WKPageGetScrollPinningBehavior(WKPageRef page)
2920{
2921 ScrollPinningBehavior pinning = toImpl(page)->scrollPinningBehavior();
2922
2923 switch (pinning) {
2924 case WebCore::ScrollPinningBehavior::DoNotPin:
2925 return kWKScrollPinningBehaviorDoNotPin;
2926 case WebCore::ScrollPinningBehavior::PinToTop:
2927 return kWKScrollPinningBehaviorPinToTop;
2928 case WebCore::ScrollPinningBehavior::PinToBottom:
2929 return kWKScrollPinningBehaviorPinToBottom;
2930 }
2931
2932 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2933 return kWKScrollPinningBehaviorDoNotPin;
2934}
2935
2936void WKPageSetScrollPinningBehavior(WKPageRef pageRef, WKScrollPinningBehavior pinning)
2937{
2938 CRASH_IF_SUSPENDED;
2939 ScrollPinningBehavior corePinning = ScrollPinningBehavior::DoNotPin;
2940
2941 switch (pinning) {
2942 case kWKScrollPinningBehaviorDoNotPin:
2943 corePinning = ScrollPinningBehavior::DoNotPin;
2944 break;
2945 case kWKScrollPinningBehaviorPinToTop:
2946 corePinning = ScrollPinningBehavior::PinToTop;
2947 break;
2948 case kWKScrollPinningBehaviorPinToBottom:
2949 corePinning = ScrollPinningBehavior::PinToBottom;
2950 break;
2951 default:
2952 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2953 }
2954
2955 toImpl(pageRef)->setScrollPinningBehavior(corePinning);
2956}

2974WKMediaState WKPageGetMediaState(WKPageRef page)
2975{
2976 WebCore::MediaProducer::MediaStateFlags coreState = toImpl(page)->reportedMediaState();
2977 WKMediaState state = kWKMediaIsNotPlaying;
2978
2979 if (coreState & WebCore::MediaProducer::MediaState::IsPlayingAudio)
2980 state |= kWKMediaIsPlayingAudio;
2981 if (coreState & WebCore::MediaProducer::MediaState::IsPlayingVideo)
2982 state |= kWKMediaIsPlayingVideo;
2983 if (coreState & WebCore::MediaProducer::MediaState::HasActiveAudioCaptureDevice)
2984 state |= kWKMediaHasActiveAudioCaptureDevice;
2985 if (coreState & WebCore::MediaProducer::MediaState::HasActiveVideoCaptureDevice)
2986 state |= kWKMediaHasActiveVideoCaptureDevice;
2987 if (coreState & WebCore::MediaProducer::MediaState::HasMutedAudioCaptureDevice)
2988 state |= kWKMediaHasMutedAudioCaptureDevice;
2989 if (coreState & WebCore::MediaProducer::MediaState::HasMutedVideoCaptureDevice)
2990 state |= kWKMediaHasMutedVideoCaptureDevice;
2991 if (coreState & WebCore::MediaProducer::MediaState::HasActiveDisplayCaptureDevice)
2992 state |= kWKMediaHasActiveDisplayCaptureDevice;
2993 if (coreState & WebCore::MediaProducer::MediaState::HasMutedDisplayCaptureDevice)
2994 state |= kWKMediaHasMutedDisplayCaptureDevice;
2995
2996 return state;
2997}
